reviews.title: Worked great, but new terms of use are unacceptable.
reviews.comment: Used to love the app, works great, but now wants 2% of whatever check it loads, meaning that I load a thousand dollar paycheck, it costs me $20 instead of the $2 it used to. I am permanently discontinuing my use of the app as a result, and discourage others from using it as well. It\'s not worth it, you can still load the check on for only $2 at your local check cashing place.
reviews.author: A Google User

reviews.title: insight has gone downhill
reviews.comment: I used to love everything about this card - one monthly fee, no other fees; now I am getting charged $1 for every debit transaction. Had $300 overdraft protection; now there is none and I get charged $1 for every declined transaction - sometimes it even declines transactions for no reason when more than enough money is available. Automatic deposit used to come 3 days before payday, now it shows up on payday. Used to take 5 minutes for a check to clear in this app; now I have waited over a day. The app no longer remembers my login info when I check \'save login info\' - so from my phone, I have to login every single time I use it. I am now looking for a better card, as this one has just gone downhill. I would NOT recommend using Insight.
reviews.author: Lance Stubblefield

reviews.title: Use with caution
reviews.comment: While I once used this app without incident - quite enjoyed it in fact - the folks at Urban Trust Bank have recently let me down in a big way. While no mention of this is made in their app notes, attempts to load funds to your card involve a verification process where they contact - not the account holder\'s bank - but rather the check authors DIRECTLY to ascertain validity.  In my case this included my 93 year old grandmother late on Christmas night, and then before 8am the following day... scared and confused her A LOT! Another check I tried to deposit failed their verification 5 times, not for reasons of available funds, but because the business who issued me the check was closed for the holidays and could not answer their phone!  Now I am left with a worthless check endorsed to a bank I am starting to dislike GREATLY! USE WITH CAUTION
reviews.author: Ben Keszler
